<section class="hero">
  <h1>Forum</h1>
  <p>We use GitHub Discussions for Q&A, show-and-tell and community support. It?s free, searchable and easy to join.</p>
</section>
<section class="article">
  <h2>How to participate</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Browse categories (Beginners, Health, Operations, Data & Sensing, Environment).</li>
    <li>Search before posting; add clear titles and context.</li>
    <li>Share photos or logs (avoid personal data).</li>
    <li>Mark helpful replies as answers.</li>
    <li>Be kind; assume good intent.</li>
    <li>Flag spam or unsafe advice.</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>Code of Conduct (summary)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Respectful, inclusive language.</li>
    <li>No harassment or discrimination.</li>
    <li>No medical or hazardous chemical advice beyond official guidance.</li>
    <li>Credit sources; no plagiarism.</li>
    <li>Moderators may edit/close threads to keep discussions constructive.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><a class="badge" href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Discussions</a></p>
</section>

